		<td><b>Another palette test</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I wanted a palette test ROM that would work with FCEUX, and I couldn't find one digging around so I made a new one.<br /><br />This displays the regular palette on the top, and lets you play with emphasis/greyscale bits for the palette on the bottom. You can also toggle the &quot;forbidden black&quot; $0D color.<br /><br />I tested it on a bunch of different emulators, and on my NTSC NES. It should presumably work with Dendy. The PAL version of the ROM has only been tested in emulators.<br /><br /><em>Edit:</em> added PAL version. 2018-7-26<br /><br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<span class="gensmall"><b>File comment:</b> Palette test video capture</span><br />
		
