		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In response to a request in <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=13252&amp;start=15#p155588" class="postlink">another thread</a>, I've made a simple ROM for displaying a full-screen colour. (No special tricks, should run on any NES, NTSC or PAL or whatever.)<br /><br />You can select any of the 64 entries, toggle emphasis and greyscale bits, and hide the display if you just want a full screen of a single colour.<br /><br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<span class="gensmall"><b>File comment:</b> Color test screenshot</span><br />
		
